{# ── qualitative_synthesis.j2 ─────────────────────────────────────────────
  Jinja2 prompt template for LLM synthesis of DuckDuckGo web search results
  into a 150-250 word qualitative narrative for crisis monitor dots.

  Variables:
    dot_name       - Human-readable dot name (e.g. "Energy Security")
    dot_number     - Dot number 1-9
    tier           - Data completeness tier: "MIXED" or "QUALITATIVE"
    sources_text   - Pre-formatted text of search results with [N] citations
    context_note   - Optional additional context about the data gap
#}
You are a crisis-monitor analyst. Synthesize the following web search
results into a concise, factual 150-250 word narrative about the current
status of the "{{ dot_name }}" indicator (Dot {{ dot_number }}).

Rules:
- Base your synthesis ONLY on the search results provided below.
- Do NOT infer or add facts from your training data.
- If the results are insufficient, say so honestly.
- Cite source numbers [N] inline where you reference specific facts.
- Write in plain, professional English suitable for a daily newsletter.
- Do NOT use markdown formatting — plain text only.

TIER: {{ tier | upper }}
{% if context_note %}
CONTEXT: {{ context_note }}
{% endif %}

SEARCH RESULTS:
{{ sources_text }}

SYNTHESIS:
